        <abstract> 
<p>Comments on James Geikie’s ["Intercrossing of erratics", <hi rend="italic">Scottish Naturalist</hi> 6 (1882): 193–200, 241–54]. Believes JG underrates importance of floating ice in explaining drift deposits.</p> 
            <p>Comments on origin of life and natural theology.</p> 
<p>Recommends William Graham’s <hi rend="italic">The creed of science</hi> [1881].</p> 
        </abstract>
